main event: An unidentified object was observed in the sky over Mollala, Oregon on 26 October 1965.
interesting points: The object was noted to be a small, round dot smaller than a star or planet,It was observed moving from an NNE to SSW direction over Portland,The object was suspected to be the KPS-2 satellite,It was visible to the naked eye and through binoculars,The witness reported seeing the object at least five times previously.
sighted object: small round dot in the sky
witness description: a teacher looking for the object
